{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"918c","heading":"Rural and remote communities electrification grants","label":"918c Rural and remote communities electrification grants","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s918c","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/ch31/schI","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs918c","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":["Editorial Notes","CodificationSection was enacted as part of the Public Utility Regulatory Policies Act of 1978, and not as part of the Rural Electrification Act of 1936 which comprises this chapter.","Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","DefinitionsSecretary means the Secretary of Energy, see , Conservation.section 2602(14) of Title 16"],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"a","heading":"Definitions","label":"a Definitions","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s918c/a","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s918c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs918c%2Fa","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s918c/a/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s918c/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs918c%2Fa%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The term “eligible grantee” means a local government or municipality, peoples’ utility district, irrigation district, and cooperative, nonprofit, or limited-dividend association in a rural area.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s918c/a/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s918c/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs918c%2Fa%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The term “incremental hydropower” means additional generation achieved from increased efficiency after , at a hydroelectric dam that was placed in service before .January 1, 2005January 1, 2005","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s918c/a/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s918c/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs918c%2Fa%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s918c/a/3/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s918c/a/3","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs918c%2Fa%2F3%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"a renewable energy source; or","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s918c/a/3/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s918c/a/3","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs918c%2Fa%2F3%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"hydrogen, other than hydrogen produced from a fossil fuel, that is produced from a renewable energy source.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"4","heading":null,"label":"4","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s918c/a/4","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s918c/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs918c%2Fa%2F4","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s918c/a/4/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s918c/a/4","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs918c%2Fa%2F4%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"wind;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s918c/a/4/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s918c/a/4","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs918c%2Fa%2F4%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"ocean waves;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"C","heading":null,"label":"C","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s918c/a/4/C","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s918c/a/4","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs918c%2Fa%2F4%2FC","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"biomass;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"D","heading":null,"label":"D","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s918c/a/4/D","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s918c/a/4","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs918c%2Fa%2F4%2FD","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"solar;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"E","heading":null,"label":"E","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s918c/a/4/E","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s918c/a/4","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs918c%2Fa%2F4%2FE","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"landfill gas;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"F","heading":null,"label":"F","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s918c/a/4/F","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s918c/a/4","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs918c%2Fa%2F4%2FF","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"incremental hydropower;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"G","heading":null,"label":"G","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s918c/a/4/G","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s918c/a/4","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs918c%2Fa%2F4%2FG","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"livestock methane; or","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"H","heading":null,"label":"H","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s918c/a/4/H","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s918c/a/4","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs918c%2Fa%2F4%2FH","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"geothermal energy.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"5","heading":null,"label":"5","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s918c/a/5","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s918c/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs918c%2Fa%2F5","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The term “rural area” means a city, town, or unincorporated area that has a population of not more than 10,000 inhabitants.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"b","heading":"Grants","label":"b Grants","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s918c/b","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s918c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs918c%2Fb","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s918c/b/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s918c/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs918c%2Fb%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"increasing energy efficiency, siting or upgrading transmission and distribution lines serving rural areas; or","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s918c/b/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s918c/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs918c%2Fb%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"providing or modernizing electric generation facilities that serve rural areas.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"c","heading":"Grant administration","label":"c Grant administration","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s918c/c","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s918c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs918c%2Fc","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s918c/c/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s918c/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs918c%2Fc%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The Secretary shall make grants under this section based on a determination of cost-effectiveness and the most effective use of the funds to achieve the purposes described in subsection (b).","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s918c/c/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s918c/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs918c%2Fc%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"For each fiscal year, the Secretary shall allocate grant funds under this section equally between the purposes described in paragraphs (1) and (2) of subsection (b).","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s918c/c/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s918c/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs918c%2Fc%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"In making grants for the purposes described in subsection (b)(2), the Secretary shall give preference to renewable energy facilities.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"d","heading":"Authorization of appropriations","label":"d Authorization of appropriations","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s918c/d","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s918c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs918c%2Fd","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"There is authorized to be appropriated to the Secretary to carry out this section $20,000,000 for each of fiscal years 2006 through 2012.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}
